access: There is a roof shared by all tenants as well as a backyard
additional_house_rules:
I ask that you keep your fun respectful of my neighbors
- Guests are allowed in my building, but as you might know, AIRBNB is under attack in NYC, so please understand that you are just a friend looking after my home while I'm away versus a customer! I will make sure you feel at home in my space, so please just have respect for the space and the community in the building
description:
A few blocks from the most reliable train in Brooklyn, my home is comfy, colorful, & fun!

Fantastic for a getaway to NYC with all the amenities you need. The building has a gorgeous backyard and rooftop for outdoor time and is quiet at night (unlike most of the city)! Complete with wifi, a washer/dryer, dishwasher, over/stove, & built-in AC and heat, I'm sure you will feel right at home!

With tons of fun collectibles, clothes, & funky decor, my home is the perfect backdrop for your NYC trip!

My space is decked out with funky objects everywhere. It's a great spot for taking photos and every time you walk into a room you'll notice something new.

It's really cozy and a great place to hang out at the end of a long day!

The second bedroom can be turned into a bedroom with an air mattress. If you are needing one you can either get it or alert me and I'll have one shipped!

There is a roof shared by all tenants as well as a backyard

I'll be gone when you are there but completely available by phone or text. I usually will have a friend on call if you run into any problems during your stay!

Bed Stuy is so quiet and so easily accessed by the city. The apartment is really close to the JMZ subway train which takes you into manhattan.

I recommend Chez Alex, a cafe on the corner of Madison and Ralph. They have great coffee and sandwiches.

The house is near the JMZ trains on Broadway at Gates Avenue. These trains always run frequently (generally under 10 minutes).

hosts.about:
Hi! My name is Nicky and I'm an artist/muralist originally from Los Angeles. I moved to New York two years ago and have finally settled in my favorite area of Brooklyn, Bed Stuy! I'm all about having fun and my apartment is a huge reflection of my favorite things, so here's a little rundown on who I am:

Favorite Artist: Roy Lichtenstein or Andy Warhol
Favorite Movie: Austin Powers or Zoolander
Favorite Music: 90s/2000s Pop & Hip Hop
Favorite Cartoon: Spongebob Squarepants
Favorite Food: Dollar Slice (down the street)
Favorite Hobby: Painting & watching documentaries
Favorite Book: 'Just Kids' by Patti Smith
Favorite Store: Patricia Field (Bowery & Houston)
Favorite City: Tokyo, Japan

Feel free to find me on social media!
Instagram/(SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN): @nickyottav
